Legend: [x] done  [ ] not started  [p] in progress  [!] needs revisit

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
PRE-BETA  (must be working before any beta users)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

[ ] Reset password on login screen — Severity: High
    No "Forgot password?" link on login page. No reset-password endpoint or frontend flow exists.
    Requires: reset token table, POST /api/auth/forgot-password + /api/auth/reset-password endpoints,
    frontend forgot-password component and route.
    Blocked by: email provider must be configured (SENDGRID_API_KEY set in prod env).

[ ] Stripe integration — Severity: High
    No payment processing exists. Users cannot upgrade or downgrade plans.
    Requires: Stripe Checkout session creation endpoint, webhook handler to update
    users.subscription_tier on payment success/failure, frontend upgrade flow in settings.

[!] Appointment reminders — Severity: High
    Marked done but INCOMPLETE. Booking confirmation email fires on appointment
    create/update (notifications service), but scheduled reminders are NOT auto-created.
    The reminders table and CRUD exist but nothing creates reminder records automatically.
    Requires: auto-create reminder record(s) on appointment save (e.g. 24h before), and a
    background job or cron to send them when they come due.

[p] Email notifications — Severity: High
    SendGrid is wired and booking confirmations fire. Invoice sending works.
    Remaining: SENDGRID_API_KEY must be set in the production environment.
    Needs testing end-to-end in prod before beta.

[ ] Business settings — email receipt message — Severity: Medium
    Invoice message (shown on invoice PDF/email) is implemented. A separate configurable
    email receipt/footer message for outbound emails does not exist yet.
    Requires: additional field in business_settings table + UI in Business settings tab.

[ ] Account lockout after N failures — Severity: Medium
    No per-account brute-force protection. IP rate limiter (5 req/min) exists but
    does not protect against distributed attacks targeting a single account.
    Requires: failed_login_attempts + locked_until columns on users table (migration),
    increment on bad password in auth/service.go Login, reset on success, 429 response when locked.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
V1 LAUNCH  (needed before public v1 release)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

[x] Subscription enforcement — plan limits enforced at API layer
[x] Form validation — save buttons disabled when form is invalid or submitting
[x] Invoice templates — template system built
[x] Desktop view — responsive layout restored
[x] Show/hide password toggle on login and register

[ ] Email verification — Severity: Medium
    New users are never asked to verify their email address.
    Requires: email_verified column on users, verification token table, send verification
    email on register, block certain actions until verified, resend verification UI.
    Blocked by: email provider configured in prod (same dependency as password reset).
    Implement alongside or after password reset flow.

[ ] Content-Security-Policy header — Severity: Low
    Security headers are set (X-Frame-Options, HSTS, etc.) but CSP is missing.
    Even a basic default-src 'self' would block inline script execution if XSS occurred.
    Requires: add CSP header in backend/internal/middleware/security.go.
    Small change, good hardening before public launch.

[ ] Frontend HTTP request timeouts — Severity: Low
    API calls in api.service.ts can hang indefinitely. No timeout interceptor exists.
    Requires: add a timeout() RxJS operator in a new timeout interceptor or in ApiService.
    Prevents UI from freezing on slow/dropped network.

[ ] revoked_tokens cleanup job — Severity: Low
    Expired rows accumulate in revoked_tokens table indefinitely. Index on expires_at exists.
    Requires: on startup goroutine (or pg_cron) running
    DELETE FROM revoked_tokens WHERE expires_at < NOW() periodically.

